page.title: 06Wildlife
page.content: ECOLOGY IN DELABOLE AREA {Birds & habitats.}By David Barrett. { FARMLAND.} There are usually kestrels hovering above the crops.There are a lot of herring gulls and black headed gulls which wait until the fields are being ploughed so they can get the worms and seeds.{ { WOODLAND. } Some buzzards live in the wood.I have seen a green woodpecker and a lesser spotted woodpecker.Sometimes in the night,you can hear and see tawny owls.Blackbirds and thrushes run along the ground looking for insects.You can see magpies flying over the trees. {SEACOAST. Along the coasts you can see Razorbills,Guillemots,Lesser & Great Black-backed gulls,fulmars,cormorants and shags.
